    "[53,54]) to make it clear to students what SDG will be integrated into the course.",
    "Following a similar approach, universities can also take a top-down approach to require all course lectures to indicate clearly on the course outlines which GenAI can be used in each course and to what extent.",
    "For instance, (i) prohibit all use of AI tools, (ii) use only with prior permission, (iii) use only with explicit acknowledgment, and (iv) freely use with no acknowledgment is needed.",
    "This can avoid potential conflict in using GenAI for course activities or assignments.Third, this study suggests universities prepare and release guidelines for both teachers and students, instead of only one side.",
